Date: 20/2/1937
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 106
Edition:
Quote: Although it is not extensively cultivated at the present time, it may be grown successfully in certain portions of this Dominion, not only for ornamental purposes, but with profit to the grower, as the fruits - commonly known as Chinese gooseberries - find a ready sale with an increasing demand at 6d to 9d per pound.
